# Alembic migrations

Run all commands from `backend/` with the virtualenv active.

## Database URL

`alembic/env.py` reads `DATABASE_URL` via `app.config.settings.database.database_url` — same source as `app/database.py`. No hardcoded connection string in `alembic.ini`.

## target_metadata

`Base.metadata` from `app/database.py`. When models exist (Step 4+), import them in `alembic/env.py` and/or `app/models/__init__.py` so autogenerate detects tables.

## Commands (Windows / PowerShell)

```powershell
cd backend
.venv\Scripts\activate

# Check current revision
.venv\Scripts\alembic current

# List migration history
.venv\Scripts\alembic history

# Create a new migration (after models exist — Step 4+)
.venv\Scripts\alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

# Apply all pending migrations
.venv\Scripts\alembic upgrade head

# Roll back one revision
.venv\Scripts\alembic downgrade -1
```

Step 3.3 ships an empty **baseline** revision to verify the pipeline. Business tables come in Step 4.x.
